<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--KitchenGunshot     12-26 0165</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Kitchen Gunshot,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Killed With Shot Through Kitchen Window</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man reaching for sugar from his kitchen cabinet
was killed by shots fired through his second floor window, police
said.
   Inacio Mendez, 43, of Boston's Roxbury section was pronounced
dead at Boston City Hospital on Christmas night, about 45 minutes
after the shooting, said Police Sgt. Albert Goslin.
   Goslin said Mendez's wife was sitting at the kitchen table with
her husband when he got up to make coffee. He was standing by the
window, getting sugar from the cabinet, when she heard several shots
and saw her husband grab his chest. He was hit twice _ in the left
breast and in the left arm _ but managed to stagger into a hallway
before he collapsed, Goslin said.
   Police said they had no suspects. A closed set of venetian blinds
covered the window, leading police to surmise that the gunman may
not even have known whom he was firing at.
</TEXT>
