<HEAD>Teen-ager Granted Wish To Visit Washington Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An ailing teen-ager whose wish to visit
Washington was granted last week died of cancer at his home
Christmas night, family members said today.
   Jason Brady, 16, died at at his home in Moore.
   Brady, the son of Robert and Irla Brady, suffered from Burkitts
Lymphoma and learned in early December that he had only a few weeks
to live. He wanted to visit Washington and the Make-A-Wish
Foundation in Oklahoma City arranged for the visit.
   In Washington, Brady met with President-elect George Bush,
Oklahoma Sens. Don Nickles and David Boren and appeared on the
NBC-TV ``Today Show'' with Willard Scott. He returned to Oklahoma on
Wednesday.
   A funeral service is scheduled for Wednesday morning in Moore.
