<HEAD>Customs Dog Sniffs Out Marijuana in Lamp Stands</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police have arrested a Japanese for allegedly
smuggling 11 pounds of marijuana in lamp stands.
   Masatoshi Saito was arrested after returning from Manila Dec. 20
when a dog used by customs sniffed out the marijuana in the
pedestals of three lamp stands he was carrying, said a police
official at the New Tokyo International Airport at Narita.
   Saito, 38, told investigators he bought the stands at a
department store in Manila and did not know anything about the
marijuana, valued at $200,000, said the official.
   The maximum penalty for smuggling marijuana into Japan is seven
years in prison.
