<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Ireland-Fire,0126</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four Die In Fire at Home, Parents Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRAY, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through a home in the seaside
town of Bray on Monday, killing four children and injuring their
parents, police said.
   Catherine Cassidy, 31, was hospitalized in critical condition
with burns, and her 32-year-old husband, John, suffered superficial
burns.
   Firefighters rescued their 8-year-old son, John, who suffered
smoke inhalation, police said.
   The dead were identified as Lisa, 9, and her brothers, Jason, 6,
Keith, 4, and 18-month-old Graham.
   Firefighters said the blaze in this town about 12 miles southeast
of Dublin could have been caused by an electrical fault or an open
flame.
   ``The house just seemed to go up like paper,'' a neighbor said.
</TEXT>
