<HEAD>Nuclear Plant Releases Radioactive Gas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HADDAM, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A nuclear power plant accidentally released
radioactive gas during a test today, but there were no injuries
reported, a spokeswoman said.
   ``An unplanned momentary radioactive gas release occurred,'' said
Barbara Luce, a spokeswoman for Northeastern Utilities. She said she
did not know how much gas was released at the Connecticut Yankee
nuclear power plant.
   The gas release occurred at 9:03 a.m. ``during routine sampling
from the primary system at the plant,'' Luce said.
   Plant technicians were assessing the impact, Luce said, adding
that state and other government officials had been notified as
required by law.
