<HEAD>First Couple Observe Quiet Holiday At New Home</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan and his wife Nancy spent the
Christmas holiday behind the walls of the five-bedroom home on St.
Cloud Road in fashionable Bel Air where they will live after the
president leaves office Jan. 20.
   The Reagans flew to California from Washington on Friday and will
return to the White House Jan. 5 after a New Year's stint in the
Palm Springs area.
   Assistant White House Press Secretary Mark Weinberg said Monday
he had no new information on the Reagans' private Christmas
observance Sunday.
   Mrs. Reagan had said in advance that they planned to exchange
gifts of furnishings for the house and have a traditional turkey
dinner with daughter, Maureen; her husband, Dennis Revell; son Ron;
and his wife, Doria.
   The Reagans' daughter, Patti, is estranged from her parents and
the president's son, Michael, and his family, were said to have
visited them on Saturday.
