<2ND_LINE>AM-Afghanistan,0196</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Afghan Guerrilla Leader Meets Iranian Officials</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Afghanistan's Shiite guerrilla leader
Burhanuddin Rabbani on Monday met Iranian officials and thanked them
for their support, Iranian television reported.
   The broadcast, monitored in Nicosia, said Rabbani briefed Iranian
Prime Minister Hussein Musavi and Parliament Speaker Hashemi
Rafsanjani on military developments in Afghanistan and thanked them
for their support.
   Musavi was quoted as telling Rabbani that the fight by Afghan
