Nicosia, said Afghan refugees in Iran would rally Tuesday to mark
the ninth anniversary of the Soviet intervention in Afghanistan.
   Soviet troops marched into the country in December 1979 to
support the Marxist government.
   U.S.-backed Afghan guerrillas are split into two coalitions _ the
Iran-based Shiite alliance and the larger Sunni Moslem alliance
based in Pakistan.
