<HEAD>Retired Chief Justice Hospitalized</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Retired Chief Justice Warren E. Burger has been
hospitalized since Sunday suffering from what a Supreme Court
spokeswoman said was dehydration, exhaustion and ``mild touch of
pneumonia.''
   Burger, 81, was admitted to Sibley Memorial Hospital here on
Christmas morning and expected to be released late Tuesday or early
Wednesday, court spokeswoman Toni House said Monday.
   ``He's in good spirits and he described his illness as a new rare
disease, `Bicentennial exhaustion,''' Ms. House said.
   Burger has chaired the Constitutional Bicentennial Commission
since retiring in 1986 as chief justice following a 17-year career
on the high court.
   He was admitted to the hospital last year for ``back spasms,''
treated and released.
