<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Gorbachev     12-26 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Gorbachev,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gorbachev Reappears After Rare 15-Day Absence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Mikhail S. Gorbachev reappeared in public
Monday after a rare, 15-day absence from public events and Soviet TV
news coverage.
   In news film of his meeting Monday with Herbert Mies, head of the
West German Communist Party, Gorbachev appeared smiling, rested and
healthy _ in contrast to the shocked and saddened visage he showed
after viewing the carnage in earthquake-stricken Armenia on Dec. 11.
   Since then, he had not been shown on television, nor reported as
attending any public event. He missed no scheduled event, but for
Gorbachev to be absent from public view for so long is rare.
   Gorbachev's meeting Monday with Mies included a discussion of his
forthcoming visit to West Germany in the first half of 1989.
</TEXT>
